~minder's on point, and in line with many other sources. Acceleration is pushing us away from tradition so fast that there is no time for evaluation of impact, no time for course correction.

We (as a species) have been carefully inching across the tightrope of sustainability for a hundred thousand years, but are now sprinting ahead at unprecedented speed. Maybe we've already made a misstep and are now falling, but still moving forward fast enough to not have noticed yet.